\section {Random Dirichlet series}

 A classical result due to Selberg states that the distribution of the Riemann zeta function on the critical line is asymptotically Gaussian, after suitable renormalisation. More precisely, the distribution of
$
\left\{ \left(\frac{1}{2}\log\log (T)\right)^{-1/2}\log|\zeta(1/2+it)|\; :\; t\in [0,T]\right\}
$
